# Agent coding standards

Before non-trivial edits, read **`AGENT_CODING_RULES.txt`** at the repository root. It is the full canonical list (items 1–42).

**Hard requirements (summary):**

- Do not duplicate logic to mask a bug; fix root cause.
- Match existing architecture, naming, and patterns; no drive-by refactors or unrelated files.
- Trace call chains and data lifecycle; consider null/empty, edges, concurrency, and blast radius.
- No unnecessary dependencies; no hardcoded env-specific URLs/secrets/ports.
- Prefer failing tests first, then fix; verify boundaries and unhappy paths.
- One concern per change; do not mix refactors with bug fixes in the same PR.
- Do not swallow errors or hide failures; handle API timeouts and failures explicitly.
- Document assumptions and uncertainty; re-read your diff before submitting.

If anything in this rule conflicts with the text file, **the text file wins**.
